<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment Rate Up in Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The number of jobless in Ukraine
reached 1.2 million by the end of August, which accounting for
3.08 percent of the workforce, the Interfax news agency reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate in the first eight months of 1998
increased by 50 percent over the same period of last year. The
rate in some states has reached five or six percent.
</P>
<P>
So far, 875,000 Ukranians have registered as unemployed, but
with only 47,000 job vacancies, an average 18 jobless people will
compete for each post.
</P>
<P>
Economists here attributed the soaring of the unemployment rate
to the decline in production. They said that the real number of
the jobless was much more than the official figure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
