<HEADLINE> Demonstrations Continue in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Supporters of the opposition
Albanian Democratic Party Wednesday held another demonstration in
the Tirana's main Skanderbeg Square despite a police prohibition
order.
</P>
<P>
At 11:00 local time, more than 1,000 Democrats and their
supporters marched to the square shouting anti-government
slogans. The march was led by Sali Berisha, chairman of the
Democratic Party, who held a press conference at party headquarters
earlier that morning.
</P>
<P>
Berisha addressed at the rally, again demanding the resignation
of Prime Minister Fatos Nano.
</P>
<P>
Although the police had repeatedly announced the prohibition of
any demonstration or rally, they held back when the marchers
approached to avoid more clashes and the demonstration passed
peacefully.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian parliament will discuss annulling parliamentary
immunity for Berisha and other opposition leaders on Thursday
morning at the request of the Public Attorneys. 
</P>
</TEXT>
