<HEADLINE> Romanian FM on Albania and Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Romanian authorities backed
the legitimate Government in Albania and hoped that all violence
in the balkan country be stemmed.
</P>
<P>
Romanian Foreign Minister Andrei Plesu made the remarks at a
press conference on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The situation in the Kosovo province requires a stable Albania,
Plesu said, noting that Romania had never supported the parties in
dispute.
</P>
<P>
He said that he was to meet on the day with the Albanian
ambassador to Bucharest, and would hold talks with his
counterparts of Albania and Yugoslavia at the current U.N. General
Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Plesu said that Romania believed the solution to the Kosovo
risis needed to be found within Yugoslavia's borders.  
</P>
</TEXT>
