<HEADLINE> Suspects of Bank Robbery Captured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Three suspects of a bank
robbery in this capital of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region have been captured, with the majority of the
robbered money recovered, according to police sources.
</P>
<P>
Also caught is another person found to have helped harbor the
suspects. And a pistol and ten bullets have also been seized.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigations have shown that the three suspects, Zou
Liqing, Zou Lilun and Zou Zhijun, who are brothers and sister from
Renshou County of southwestern Sichuan Province, robbed a business
outlet of the Urumqi Commercial Bank at the North Xinhua Road
of Urumqi at around 9:25 p.m on September 11.
</P>
<P>
The suspects killed one person and wounded another before they
fled with more than 690,000 yuan (83,000 US dollars) in a taxi.
</P>
<P>
One of the suspects has confessed that the pistol used in
the robbery was stolen from somewhere.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said that 680,000 of the robbered money has been
recovered and the case is still being investigated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
