<HEADLINE> Daimler-Benz Donates 5 Million Marks to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Germany's largest industrial
concern Daimler-Benz AG said Wednesday that it has made a three
million mark (1.8 million U.S. dollar) cash contribution plus two
million marks (1.2 million dollars) worth of self-made equipment
to help flood victims in central and northeast China.
</P>
<P>
"We are very sorry about the tragedy that has struck so many
Chinese families. We sincerely hope that our donations will
alleviate some of the people's suffering as well as contribute to
a long-term solution for the future," Eike Lippold, chief
executive of Daimler-Benz Northeast Asia, was quoted by a
statement issued by the company as saying.
</P>
<P>
The statement also said the Daimler-Benz-manufactured
equipment, such as helicopters and vehicles, will be selected
together with the Chinese government to suit the various needs of
relief efforts and will be delivered over the next few years to
cope with the rebuilding of the effected areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
