said that on the eve of Jewish new year, which will begin
on Sunday, the army has significantly boosted its forces in
the country.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Israel will continue its activities against
terrorist groups and their leaders.
</P>
<P>
Israeli security forces killed two Hamas military wing
leaders near the West Bank city of Hebron last Thursday. And
Hamas leaders have threatened to avenge the deaths.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Hamas spiritual leader Sheikh Ahmed Yassin said on
Wednesday that those who ordered the killing of Hamas members
should be afraid of their safety.
</P>
<P>
He also said that Hamas will continue its attacks against
Israeli targets until all of Palestine is liberated. 
</P>
