<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Recaptures 4 Villages in Northern S. Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The West African peace-keeping
force ECOMOG has recaptured four villages in northern Sierra
Leone earlier this week, killing at least 10 rebels, a report
from Freetown said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted local missionaries as saying that heavily
armed ECOMOG troops from Guinea recaptured the villages of
Kanathortor, Kakula, Kathiteneh and Yabaha in Kambia district in
northern Sierra Leone Monday.
</P>
<P>
No civil casualties were reported, as most residents had fled
after rebel troops attacked and seized the villages Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The fighting in Kambia is part of ECOMOG's efforts to mop up
the rebels, which were chased out of Freetown in February but has
since held out in the northern and eastern parts of the country,
where difficult terrains are hampering ECOMOG's operations.
</P>
</TEXT>
