<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-16 16:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian FM Stresses Political Means to Deal with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister
Kamal Kharrazi on Wednesday stressed that priority should be
given to political and peaceful means rather than military
actions against the Afghan Taliban militia.
</P>
<P>
"Before taking military actions against the Taliban, a chance
should be given to political and peaceful approaches in order to
protect the country's national interests," Kharrazi told the
official news agency IRNA.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks after Iranian supreme leader Ayatollah
Ali Khamenei on Tuesday ordered the armed forces to be on the
alert and the Iranian army, the Islamic Revolutionary Guards
Corps (IRGC), security and Basij (volunteer) forces announced
their readiness to carry out military actions against the
Taliban.
</P>
<P>
Observers here regard Kharrazi's remarks as a signal that the
moderate government of President Mohammad Khatami preferred
political means to solve the tension between Iran and the Taliban
following the killing of nine Iranian diplomats in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi said that the Iranian Foreign Ministry has launched
intensive diplomatic efforts at international and regional level
and the results have been sensed in terms of some pressures
exerted on the Taliban to stop massacre in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Iran has so far exercised restraint, but its patience has
limits, he said, expressing hope that the Taliban would not lose
the chance which would pass like a cloud.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said that as recommended by Khamenei,
all avenues would be utilized to protect the country's national
interests and the enemies would not be allowed to reach their
ominous goals.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme National Security Council (SNSC) is in charge of
adopting plans and the staff members of the Foreign Ministry would
carry out their duties to secure stability in the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei on Tuesday called on officials of the country,
including the armed forces, to be ready for "speedy, timely and
decisive implementation of whatever decisions the senior
political and security authorities deem necessary and right for
the country."
</P>
<P>
Khamenei's call was echoed throughout the country by
statements of readiness to carry out his order.
</P>
<P>
The IRGC and the Iranian army have deployed over 200,000
troops along the 850-kilometer border with Afghanistan following
the tension between Iran and the Taliban.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian army is scheduled to launch its biggest maneuver
along the border later this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
