<HEADLINE> China, Russia to Increase Cooperation in Conversion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A three-day Russian-Chinese
Conversion and Cooperation Forum opened here on Wednesday at the
initiation of the intergovernmental Russian-Chinese commission on
trade- economic and scientific-technical cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Over 200 experts from the Russian and Chinese sides take part
in the forum sponsored by the Chinese People's Association for
Friendship with Foreign Countries and the Russian International
Center for Scientific- Cultural Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The forum is aimed at boosting cooperation between Russia and
China in converting military enterprises into civilian use and
establishing direct links between the two countries' enterprises
and organizations interested in effectively using leading
technology and advanced products.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin sent the forum a congratulating
telegram, noting that military-civilian conversion is becoming an
important part of the world's peace and disarmament efforts.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese and Russian experts made an important
step by probing new ways for the conversion cooperation, and that
the peaceful use of military technology would promote world peace,
social development and human progress in the world.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin, in his congratulating letter,
said the purpose of the big forum held by Chinese and Russian
experts in Moscow is to expand areas of cooperation, establish
long-term and steady relations between the two countries, and to
cooperate in major projects of military- to-civilian conversion.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening forum, Mikhail Titolenko, chairman of
the Russia-China Association of Friendship, pointed out that there
is still a huge potential in bilateral cooperation in the
scientific-technical, economic-trade areas, to be tapped by the
two sides.
</P>
<P>
Chinese charge d'affaires ad interim in Russia Wang Fengxiang
noted that this forum is a serious attempt to search for new areas
of equal and mutually beneficial cooperation. It shows that the
Chinese-Russian strategic partnership is being strengthened and
developed, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation, headed by Qi Huaiyuan, chairman of the
Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign
Countries, consists of more than 80 experts from various fields,
including aviation and space, shipping, electronics, nuclear
industry, petrochemistry and metallurgy and weaponry.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the opening ceremony, Russian First Deputy Prime
Minister Yury Maslyukov met with Qi Huaiyuan and other leaders of
the Chinese delegation in the government building. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
