border dispute between the two countries erupted last May,
according to local reports.
</P>
<P>
Eritrea said earlier up to 17,000 of its nationals had been
expelled from Ethiopia since the border dispute. However,
Ethiopia said those deported for security reasons were only
around 4,000.  
