<HEADLINE> Russia Launches Intercontinental Ballistic Missile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Russia on Wednesday launched
an intercontinental ballistic missile from the Plesetsk cosmodrome
in northern Russia, the Strategic Missile Force said.
</P>
<P>
The PC-12M missile, launched at 15:10 local time (11:10GMT),
hit an exercise target in the area of Kamchatka in the Far East,
the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The success of the launch meant that the missile, commissioned
more than 10 years ago, remained intact in terms of its technical
and military qualities.
</P>
<P>
"The launch once again convincingly proved the high combat
readiness of the force and the reliability and technical readiness
of intercontinental ballistic missiles of this type," the press
service of the Strategic Missile Force said.
</P>
<P>
"All the previous 57 launches of Topol systems were successful
after the completion of joint flight tests," the press service
added.
</P>
<P>
The launch was part of Russia's efforts to prolong the service
life of the Topol missile system, Interfax said. 
</P>
