<HEADLINE> Simitis, Prodi, Nano Exchange Views on Albanian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Greek Prime Minister Costas
Simitis Wednesday discussed respectively with his Italian and
Albanian counterparts, Romano Prodi and Fatos Nano, the political
situation in neighboring Albania.
</P>
<P>
In his phone conversations, Simitis said that whatever solution
arises must be the result of cooperation and dialogue, the
semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The premier expressed his opposition to the use of violence,
and stressed the need for maintenance of order and regard for
democratic procedures.
</P>
<P>
Simitis also told Nano that Greece was willing to help Albania
at this critical moment.
</P>
<P>
At least three people have been killed and 14 wounded in the
Violent clashes in Tirana which were touched off by the weekend
slaying of a leading Albanian opposition deputy Azem Hajdari.
</P>
