<HEADLINE> Vietnam Exports 2.98 Million Tons of Rice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has exported 2.98
million tonnes of rice so far this year, according to reports on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Traders have quoted 25 percent broken grade rice at 280
U.S. dollars to 285 dollars per ton.
</P>
<P>
There are almost no orders for the five percent broken grade
which is being exported for 310 dollars to 315 dollars per ton
under the contracts signed before August 14 when the government
issued a temporary ban on the export of fresh rice.
</P>
<P>
A representative of the Southern Food Corporation was in
Indonesia to bid for the supply of 400,000 tons of rice for that
country late this year and in early 1999.
</P>
<P>
However, Indonesia wants to import rice on deferred payment
which is almost unacceptable for Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
