<HEADLINE> Two World Records Fall at Asian Weightlifting Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, China, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese
weightlifters broke two world records and one junior world record
at the 3rd Asian Junior Women's and the 11th Asian Junior Men's
Weightlifting Championships here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 53-kg category, Zhang Xixiang snatched 95
kilograms to beat the previous world record of 92.5 kilograms.
She garnered a total of 207.5 kilograms, also beat the previous
world mark of 205 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
In the 11th Junior Men's Asian Championships, Peng Chongdong o
f China broke the world youth record of 175 kilograms with a lift
of 175.5 kilograms in the clean and jerk competitions of the
62-kilogram class.
</P>
<P>
China made a clean sweep of the nine golds at stake today in
the three classes including women's 53kg, 58kg and men's 62kg.
</P>
</TEXT>
