<HEADLINE> China Able to Meet Housing Construction Goals, Says Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- China can meet its goals for
housing construction this year, Vice-Minister of Construction Song
Chunhua said here today.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident about meeting this year's goals for housing
construction and believe that this sector will help boost the
national economic growth rate by more than one percentage point,"
he said at a meeting on China's economy and investment environment.
</P>
<P>
China plans to build 212 million square meters of efficiency
residential housing this year, with a total investment exceeding
170.3 billion yuan, according to Song.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that China's total investment in real
estate rose 15 percent on a yearly basis in the first seven months
this year, with investment in residential housing development
during the period surging 22.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Housing sales in terms of floor space for the January-July
period jumped 51.3 percent from a year ago, while
sales volume for the seven-month period soared 65.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Song said China's housing market has huge potential and the
market potential for efficiency housing, greatly needed by medium-
and low-income families, is still greater.
</P>
<P>
"Housing consumption will continue to rise in the time to
come," he said.
</P>
<P>
China's per capita living housing space for urban residents
will reach nine square meters by the end of this year, up from 8.8
square meters last year, according to Song. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
