<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine Grain Output to Reach 30 Million Tons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine's grain yield this year
will reach 30 million tons, five million tons fewer than last
year, Minister of Agriculture-Industry Complexes Boris Supikhanov
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Supikhanov told the Ukraine parliament that the figure was
higher than what was previously forecast by economists.
</P>
<P>
According to Ukrainian Interfax News Agency, Supikhanov
attributed this year's reduction in grain output to droughts in
eastern and central regions and excessive rains in the west and
north. Meanwhile rains and storms destroyed one million hectares
of crops, and dramatically reduced the output of two million
hectares of fields.
</P>
<P>
Supikhanov also said more than 14 million tons of winter wheat
have been harvested so far, ensuring this year's bread supply.
Last year's winter wheat output was 18.4 million tons, Supikhanov
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
