<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sam Rainsy Party Agrees to Join Assembly Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SIEM REAP, Cambodia, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The leader of one
of Cambodia's two main opposition parties, Sam Rainsy, said
Thursday that his party would take part in the convention of a new
parliament and the three-party summit hosted by King Norodom
Sihanouk.
</P>
<P>
The announcement came after a four-hour meeting between Sam
Rainsy and the King, which he described as "cordial and
satisfactory".
</P>
<P>
He said that the Sam Rainsy Party (SRP) supported the King's
decision to host the summit. He believed that the King could play
an important role as a coordinator.
</P>
<P>
"But we did not touch upon the formation of the new
government," Sam Rainsy said.
</P>
<P>
Sam Rainsy said he placed great hope in the summit which is
scheduled to open on September 22 in Siem Reap. If the three
parties reach an agreement, the situation in Cambodia might
then return to normal.
</P>
<P>
A communique released by Royal Palace Thursday showed that the
National Assembly was scheduled to be convened on September 24,
after which the members of parliament are expected to be sworn in
at the famous Angkor Wat temple nearby.
</P>
<P>
The leaders of the three main parties agreed to participate in
the summit. They are Chea Sim and Hun Sen, President and
Vice-President of the Cambodian People's Party, Prince Ranariddh,
President of Funcinpec, and Sam Rainsy of the SRP.
</P>
<P>
"The SRP is a small party in the Assembly," Sam Rainsy said.
"So we can not resist two other main parties in principle. We are
not strong enough to have any influence over them.
</P>
<P>
"But we will stick to the election complaints and seek for them
to be resolved fairly. I will also ask to discuss civil rights at
the meeting such as the freedom of movement of opposition leaders
and members of Parliament which was banned by the Government," he
added.
</P>
<P>
A communique released by Funcinpec on the same day appealed to
all governments, particularly members of Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN), friends of Cambodia, and the European Union
to immediately intervene on behalf of those whose fundamental
right of movement had been violated.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sam Rainsy expressed his concern that if the crisis
could not be solved satisfactorily, the protesters would take to
the streets again.
</P>
<P>
"The Funcinpec party has agreed to participate in the new
National Assembly's first session scheduled on September 24
presided over by the King in Siem Reap," Prince Ranariddh said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the prince confirmed that Funcinpec has not altered
its demand that the discrepancy between the printed ballots (nine
million) and registered voters (5.4 million) be accounted for and
a seat allocation formula that appeared in the early version of
election documents be adopted.
</P>
<P>
He also hoped to meet Chea Sim as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
He then warned the continuation of demonstrations will depend
on the outcome of the three-party summit although the Funcinpec
party had decided to call off protests in order to pave the way
for the summit.
</P>
<P>
The two main opposition parties Funcinpec and the SRP have been
protesting what they call election violations in the polls of July
26.
</P>
<P>
At least two people have been killed in clashes with the police
and many more injured since the government clamped down on
unauthorized protests last Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
