<HEADLINE> Seven Killed in Building Collapse in Karachi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 17 (Xinhua) -- At least seven people are
reported to have been killed when a stone-made three-storey
building collapsed in the south port city of Karachi Thursday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
According to the Associated Press of Pakistan, fire brigade
volunteers had retrieved the bodies of four men, two women and a
child from the rubbles of the collapsed building. Another four
were injured and were rushed to a nearby hospital.
</P>
<P>
Eye witnesses said the 25-year-old building, constructed on a
small plot in the "Kabari Market" area, grumbled while some
digging work was underway in one of the shops located on its
ground floor.
</P>
<P>
The diggers are reported to have reached the foundation when
the structure caved in. 
</P>
