<HEADLINE> HK Legislative Council By-Election to Be Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A Legislative Council
(LegCo) by-election for the financial services functional
constituency will be held on November 5, a spokesman for the
Registration and Electoral Office said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chim Pui-chung, former representative of the constituency in
the LegCo, was relieved of his duties as a Legislative Councilor
on September 9, after he was jailed for three years for plotting
to forge share transfer documents.
</P>
<P>
The nomination period will run from September 24 to October 7.
</P>
<P>
To qualify as a candidate for the by-election, a person has to
be a registered elector of the functional constituency, or have a
substantial connection with the constituency, said the spokesman.
</P>
