<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Grants New Aid to Palestinians and Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said
Thursday that it had approved a humanitarian aid package, worth
10.9 million ECUs (11.99 million U.S. dollars), for Palestinian
communities in the West Bank and Gaza Strip and refugees in
Jordan, Syria and Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The package also includes assistance to Lebanese affected by
the Palestinian refugee crisis.
</P>
<P>
Since Israel closed its border to Palestinians seeking jobs,
many Palestinians in the West Bank and Gaza Strip have been out of
employment and lived in poverty. Some have sought refuge in
neighboring countries, such as Jordan, Syria, and Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The aid, managed by the European Community Humanitarian Office,
will enable United Nations' agencies and European non-governmental
organizations to implement aid programs for the next six to nine
months.
</P>
<P>
The aid programs will focus on providing medicines, medical
supplies, specialized equipment, emergency rehabilitation, and
emergency food aid. They also include the training of specialist
personnel.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, the executive body of the 15-nation
European Union, also approved humanitarian aid of five million
ECUs (5.5 million dollars) for Mali and 1.4 million ECUs (1.54
million dollars) for Honduras to ease the poverty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
