<HEADLINE> Ukraine Calls for Establishment of Free Trade Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A free trade zone in the
Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) is the best way to help
Ukraine, Russia and their neighboring countries to shake off
economic crisis, said Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He is to discuss the proposal for the CIS, covering the
countries which formerly made up the Soviet Union, with Russian
President Boris Yeltsin on Friday night in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma emphasized the importance of removing all obstacles to
the plan, appealing for the scrapping of the customs union
created by Russia, Belarus, Kazakhstan and Kyrgyzstan.
</P>
<P>
The free trade zone proposal was based on the fact that the CIS
countries had closely linked national economies, he said.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma said the economic crisis would be the main priority in
his discussions with Yeltsin and new Russian Prime Minister
Yevgeny Primakov.
</P>
<P>
Russia's future course and its economic policies would have a
major influence on Ukraine, he noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980917.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKSAR Government Making Sustained Efforts to Ease Unemployment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Secretary for Education and
Manpower Joseph Wong of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR) of China said here Thursday that the SAR government
continued to be very concerned about the high and rising
unemployment and was deeply sympathetic towards those facing
employment difficulties.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated the SAR government's determination to spare no
effort in helping the unemployed to rejoin the workforce as soon
as possible.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest labor force statistics released
Thursday by the Census and Statistics Department of Hong Kong, the
provisional seasonally adjusted unemployment rate for the period
June to August 1998 was 5.0 percent, and the provisional
underemployment rate was 2.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
For the period May to July 1998, the seasonally adjusted
unemployment rate was 4.8 percent, while the underemployment rate
was 2.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the period June to August 1998 with May to July 1998,
the increase in unemployment rate occurred mainly in the
foundation and superstructure sector of the construction industry,
business services and manufacturing sectors.
</P>
<P>
As for the underemployment rate, the decrease was concentrated
in the decoration and maintenance sector of the construction
industry, and in clothing and footwear, which more than offset the
increase seen in restaurants.
</P>
<P>
Explaining the statistics, government economist K.Y. Tang said
that the continued setback in economic activity had dampened the
demand for labor. However, the entry of more school graduates into
the labor market recently had added to the labor supply. Taken
together, both factors lifted unemployment further.
</P>
<P>
Joseph Wong said that as Hong Kong is still in the midst of a
difficult economic adjustment and consolidation period brought
about largely by external economic factors, high unemployment will
"inevitably remain with us for some time."
</P>
<P>
However, Wong said, "we must not lose confidence in ourselves.
Despite the general economic downturn, there are also positive
developments in various areas."
</P>
<P>
For instance, he added, there are initial signs that Hong
Kong's tourism sector is rebounding and "we are also pressing
ahead with a number of important infrastructure and public works
projects." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980917.0127 </DOCNO>
