<HEADLINE> Lufthansa Places Major Plane Orders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The German airline Lufthansa
announced Thursday that it has ordered 42 new planes from Airbus,
Boeing Co., and the Canadian plane manufacturer Bombardier with a
total value of 2.3 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
