<HEADLINE> Boldon Wins 100 Meters at 9.88 Seconds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Ato Boldon failed to
break the world record but won the title of the men's 100 meters
with a time of 9.88 seconds at the Commonwealth Games here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Boldon, who had said he felt capable of beating the world
record of 9.84 seconds set by Donovan Bailey, threw his arms wide
and took the acclaim of the crowd. His winning time broke the
games' record of 9.91 set four years ago by Linford Christie.
</P>
<P>
Frankie Fredericks of Namibia finished second at 9.96, fo
llowed by Obadele Thompson of Barbados in the third place at
10.00. 
</P>
