<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drugs Dependents in Malaysia on Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Drug dependents in
Malaysia are on the rise according to statistics for the first
eight months this year, National Narcotics Agency Director-General
Mohd Bakri Omar said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 14,507 cases were detected during the period of
which 9,546 were new and 4,961 relapsed cases against the
altogether 36,000 cases last year, the Malaysian national news
agency Bernama quoted Mohd Bakri as saying in the northern state
of Pulau Pinang.
</P>
<P>
Selangor, a state surrounding the capital city of Kuala Lumpur,
recorded the highest number of cases this year with 2,016,
followed by Kuala Lumpur (1,928), Pahang (1,824), Johor (1,620)
and Pulau Pinang (1,457), the agency chief said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
