<DOCNO> XIE19980917.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Motorola Rolls out New Information Pager in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Motorola Inc. announced here
today that its latest information pager is now available in China
to provide Chinese stock investors with more timely and
comprehensive information.
</P>
<P>
According to Albert Lam, vice president of Motorola Greater
China Paging Subscriber Division, the new product called
"InfoMaster Plus," has a larger memory than any other information
pager on the market.
</P>
<P>
It is able to store information on up to 3,000 individual
stocks. It also incorporates graphic display functions allowing
the user to view the real-time price variations of 10 stocks.
</P>
<P>
Most individual stock investors in China have no access to
stock analysis tools which are almost exclusively accessible to
large investors at the exchanges, said Li Sen, security analyst
with the Hua Xia Security Research Institute.
</P>
<P>
She said most average investors cannot afford computers that
are installed with real-time stock trading software such as "Money
Dragon."
</P>
<P>
"Therefore," Li said, "a pager at a relatively low price with
fast transmission speed and basic stock-analysis capability has
potential in the Chinese market."
</P>
<P>
The first information pager was offered to the world by
Motorola in December 1997, said Lam, and stock traders account for
80 percent of its users.
</P>
<P>
He added that some of the functions of the new pager were
designed specially for Chinese traders.
</P>
<P>
There are now 30 million investors registered at the Shanghai
and Shenzhen Stock Exchanges, of which 95 percent are individuals
with less than 100,000 yuan invested.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
