<DOCNO> XIE19980917.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Portugal Discuss Int'l Conventions Applied in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese official said here on
Thursday that China and Portugal have reached consensus on the
continuation of international conventions which are currently
applied in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xi'an, Chinese representative in the Sino-Portuguese Joint
Liaison Group (JLG), made the remarks following a two-day JLG
meeting on Macao's participation in international conventions.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from China and Portugal began discussions on
the issue last year. Portugal submitted to the JLG a list of 205
international conventions, 78 of which have been applied in Macao.
The Portuguese side wants them to remain after Macao's return to
the motherland after 1999.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the principles of current application,
Macao's practical conditions and the guideline of "one country,
two systems," China basically agrees to the continuation of the
conventions, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
"Now that the conventions are applied in Macao, they are
components of Macao's current laws, and the continuation is
conducive to Macao's prosperity and stability," he said.
</P>
<P>
During the past two days' discussion, the two sides also talked
about conventions which are not applied in Macao but the
Portuguese side thinks can be applied and retained after Macao's
return.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that the work is more complex. The two sides will
have to work harder so as to have it completed by the end of the
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
