<HEADLINE> Southwest China City to Hold Stone Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The First China International
Stone Festival will be held in Liuzhou in southwest China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region from December 5 to 10, according
to a source from the China National Tourism Administration (CNTA).
</P>
<P>
Liuzhou is known as "the home of stones," where stones are
divided into nine categories of more than 50 varieties. The
festival will exhibit some 2,000 stones with a wide array of
features to carry forward China's traditional stone culture and
promote tourism, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Academic exchanges, auctions, and trade negotiations will also
be held during the festival.
</P>
<P>
China has a host of local products with special characteristics
of interest to tourists, such as Liuzhou stones. When this market
is developed, these products will give a strong lift to the
nation's tourism industry, according to CNTA authorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
