<HEADLINE> Dalian Wanda Retains League Title In Advance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua)-- China's soccer power Dalian
Wanda retained their league title four rounds before the end of
the season after beating Shandong Luneng 3-2 on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The win gave Dalian Wanda a unbeatable lead of 16 points over
second-placed Shanghai Shenhua.
</P>
<P>
Wanda's Swedish signing Hans Eklund opened the scoring at the
40th minute.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Li Ming made it 2-0 for the defending champions 10
minutes into the second half. Wang Peng hit in the third goal of
the game for Wanda at the 65th minute.
</P>
<P>
But the Dalian Wanda then relaxed and let the home team fought
back with two goals to cut the deficit to 3-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
