<HEADLINE> China Can Achieve Eight Percent Growth This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The goal of eight-percent
growth for China's economy can be attained this year, in spite of
the Asian financial crisis and the devastating floods in many
provinces, said a senior official from the State Development
Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
Wang Chunzheng, vice-minister of the State Development Planning
Commission, said at an economic symposium here today that a good
harvest, a stable increase in industrial output, and rapid growth
of the service sector will be achieved this year.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has taken forceful measures to increase
investment on fixed assets in the past several months. The
construction of a number of infrastructure programs is proceeding
smoothly, Wand said, adding that this will contribute a great deal
to economic growth.
</P>
<P>
"The fulfilment of China's economic growth goal will play an
important role in stablizing the Asian and global economies, and
will also pave the way for sustained economic growth in China in
the coming years," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Wang called for the deepening of reform in
state-owned enterprises and the adjustment of economic structures
to ensure high quality and rapid growth.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 delegates from more than 50 international
fund-management corporations were represented at the symposium.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
