<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Entrepreneur Donates to Qinghua University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong entrepreneur Chao
Kuang-pin today donated 1.5 million U.S. dollars to prestigious
Qinghua University in Beijing to support the university's out-reach
education program.
</P>
<P>
Qinghua University set up its out-reach program last year, a
program that enables the university to take advantage of its rich
educational resources to offer high-level part-time education
programs to technicians and administrators.
</P>
<P>
The system now has 30 networks operating outside the university
in which nearly 30 subjects are being taught including business
management, computer applications, and other high-tech
technologies. More than 800 students have already taken part in
these programs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
