<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the
Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed lower Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index fell 7.49
points to 386.55, the all-share Emas Index shed 7.49 points to
102.25, the Industrial Index lost 8.84 points to 754.39 and the
Second Board index shed 0.13 of a point to 95.52.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers by 332 to 283, while 128 counters
were unchanged, 175 others untraded and 45 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover decreased to 245.335 million shares worth
264.750 million ringgit (69.671 million U.S. dollars) from 290.022
million shares valued at 312.954 million ringgit (82.356 million
dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover declined to 236.482 million shares
worth 252.708 million ringgit (66.502 million dollars) from
Wednesday's 279.427 million shares valued at 295.100 million
ringgit (77.657 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board volume fell to 8.853 million shares worth
12.042 million ringgit (3.168 million dollars) from 10.595 million
shares valued at 17.854 million ringgit (4.698 million dollars) on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Off market turnover fell to 2.913 million shares worth 6.337
million ringgit (1.667 million dollars) from Wednesday's 27.541
million shares valued at 25.594 million ringgit (6.735 million
dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
