<HEADLINE> Germany Donates 25 Million Marks in Goods to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- German ambassador to China
Konrad Seitz, on behalf of the German government, today donated
goods worth 25 million German marks to the Chinese government for
disaster relief and post-flood reconstruction in China's flooded
areas.
</P>
<P>
He made the donation here today in a meeting with China's chief
trade negotiator Long Yongtu.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest flood-relief donation yet from a foreign
government and includes steel products, lumber, water purifiers,
water pumps, tents, vehicles, and medicines.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the German government has offered 922,000 marks to
the Red Cross Society of China and other relief organizations via
its foreign ministry.
</P>
<P>
German's Volkswagen, Siemens and Baier companies have also
provided emergency aid valued at 12 million yuan (about 1.4
million U.S. dollars) for the flood victims.  
</P>
</TEXT>
