<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Qian Qichen Meets Finnish Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Qian
Qichen said at a meeting here today with Finnish Foreign Minister
Tarja Halonen that Sino-Finnish relations have been developing
well in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Qian pointed to Halonen's discussions with several Chinese
departments on the bilateral relationship and international
issues, and said that those discussions enhanced mutual
understanding and paved the way for the upcoming China visit by
Finnish Prime Minister Paavo Lipponen.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Finland, which will be serving in
rotating presidency of the European Union (EU) in the second half
of next year, will make new contribution to the promotion of
Sino-EU cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Halonen said she was pleased to visit China as Finnish
foreign minister, and expressed satisfaction with her discussions
with relevant Chinese officials.
</P>
<P>
She noted the potential for cooperation between the two
countries, and said that Finland will join hands with China to
further mutual cooperation with her country as well as with the
European Union.
</P>
<P>
Halonen briefed Qian on her visit to Hong Kong and Macao during
her China trip. In return, Qian briefed Halonen on the current
situation in Hong Kong and preparations for the return of Macao to
China.
</P>
<P>
Qian and Halonen also exchanged views on the regional situation
and other issues of common concern. 
</P>
