<HEADLINE> Romania to Develop Rural Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian government has
decided to initiate a program for the development of education in
rural areas, Education Minister Andrei Marga said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of National Education will take all the necessary
steps to obtain an external loan to finance the program, Andrei
was quoted by the National Monitor newspaper as saying on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The main objectives of the program include the rational
development of the rural school network, the adequate endowment of
modern equipment, the creation of an efficient school
transportation network, the opening of a refectory system, the
attracting qualified teachers to rural areas with contracts for
limited periods and study credits, Andrei said.
</P>
<P>
Due to insufficient investment and the migration of teachers to
towns in recent years, education in the rural schools has become
inadequate, said the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
