<HEADLINE> Share Prices Dip on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices dipped on the
Singapore Stock Market Thursday as the benchmark Straits Times
Index (STI) shed off 12.30 points to end at 934.45 points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said market attention was focused on property stocks
after the recent prime rate cuts by leading Singapore banks.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said investors locked in their profits after the
market's massive gains over the last three days, which were
largely fueled by hopes of easing global interest rates.
</P>
<P>
However, buying activity faltered as disappointment crept after
U.S. Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan had denied that the
G-7 were drafting a co-ordinated policy that favors lower interest
rates, they noted.
</P>
<P>
The total volume was 267.86 million units worth 361.57 million
Singapore dollars (about 210.55 million U.S. dollars). Losers
outnumbered gainers by 215 to 63 with 145 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
KepLand remained the most active stock of the day as it had a
turnover of 23.96 million stocks traded. It was followed by Wing T
that had 14.73 million units done. OUB F was next with 12.11
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH was the top gainer of the day as it gained 30 cents to
close at 13.80 Singapore dollars. OUB moved up 26 cents to finish
at 2.28 Singapore dollars. OUB F was up 24 cents to end at 2.60
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 again was the biggest loser of the
day as it lost 100 cents to close at 16.70 Singapore dollars. GE
Life slid 50 cents to finish at 6.70 Singapore dollars. Venture
shed off 40 cents to end at 5.00 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
