<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Supreme Court's New Measures to Curb Judicial Corruption (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the second method, the Supreme Court will appoint
seven to nine senior and prestigious judges as "superintendents of
the Supreme Court." With authorization from the Supreme Court,
they will be empowered to supervise and offer guidance in major
and difficult trials, and in cases that are mishandled or stir
public dissent.
</P>
<P>
They will also be empowered to investigate major issues
concerning judicial corruption and cases involving parties from
different jurisdictions.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said these two measure are important moves in standardizing
the procedures of internal checks and balances, and in
strengthening the leadership of the Supreme Court over lower
courts.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also announced several steps the courts will take to curb
irregularities. For example, special efforts should be made to
stop the practice of overdue detention and delays in handling
cases, because these situations are major factors
affecting judicial fairness.
</P>
<P>
Public participation is necessary in stamping out injustice,
this is why all preliminary trials, except those excluded by law,
shall be open to the public, and a new jury system should be
instituted by selecting a large number of high quality,
knowledgeable, honest and fair jurors, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
