<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hand Grenades Detected in Vehicle in Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Police were conducting a
top-level inquiry following the detection of four hand grenades in
a vehicle parked in the basement of a twin-tower building in
Colombo-Fort Wednesday night, police sources said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The detection was made around 10 p.m. Wednesday on a tip-off,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
They quoted a senior police officer as saying that as soon as
the information was received, police searched all vehicles parked
within the basement of the twin-tower building.
</P>
<P>
The vehicle had been driven by two youths. The police were
surprised that the vehicle could pass the check point with all the
stringent security in force in the area. It is suspected that
those who manned the check point were lax in their duties.
</P>
<P>
Colombo-Fort is considered a high security zone and is on
24-hour vigil. Tamil rebels exploded two powerful car-bombs in the
zone in January, 1996 and in October last year respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
