<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Daimler-Benz to Donate Five Million DM to China's Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 ( Xinhua ) -- The Beijing branch of
Daimler-Benz of Germany, the world's leading automobile
manufacturer, will donate five million German Marks (DM) (3.3
million U.S. dollars) to China's flood-stricken areas, the
corporation announced today.
</P>
<P>
The donation consists of three million in cash and DM two
million worth of helicopters and vehicles produced by
the company. This will all be delivered to the China Charity
Federation as relief aid to the flooded areas.
</P>
<P>
Eike Lippold, chief executive officer of the Northeast Asia
branch of the corporation, said that the corporation will try
their best to help China through the difficulties and hopes to
have long-term cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese government has selected several kinds
of equipment manufactured by Daimler-Benz for the rebuilding of
the flooded areas over the next few years.  
</P>
