<HEADLINE> CPPCC Vice-Chairman Meets Hong Kong Charity Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Wang Zhaoguo, vice-chairman
of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), met here today with visitors
from the Hong Kong Tung Wah Group of Hospitals led by its chairman
Albert Cheung.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who is also head of the United Front Work Department of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, expressed
thanks to the Tung Wah Group for its contributions to charity causes
in inland areas, especially its help during the current flood rescue
and reconstruction work.
</P>
<P>
As a leading charity organization in Hong Kong, the Tung Wah
Group of Hospitals has jointly sponsored fund-raising programs
with other charity and media organizations for flood relief. A
donation worth 33 million HK dollars (4.28 million U.S. dollars)
was handed in to the Civil Affairs Ministry today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Wang said this donation by the Tung Wah Group reflects the
deep-rooted truth that blood is thicker than water between people
in the inland areas and the people of Hong Kong, and he also
briefed the visitors on the flood-fighting in the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
The Tung Wah visitors arrived in Beijing on Wednesday. They
plan to made another donation worth one-million yuan (120,000
U.S. dollars) to the earthquake victims in Zhangbei in Hebei
Province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
