<DOCNO> XIE19980917.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal, India to Hold Talks on Transit Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A seven-member Indian
delegation arrived here Thursday for talks on renewing the
Indo-Nepal Transit Treaty due to expire on December 5 this year.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day preliminary talks starting Thursday, Nepal
would raise some issues concerning the transit treaty signed seven
years ago, press reports here said.
</P>
<P>
Nepali officials were quoted as saying Nepal would demand that
the transit treaty be automatically renewed and that it use the 15
transit points in a very easy and simple way.
</P>
<P>
India has been insisting that the transit points should be
reduced due to security reasons, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The two countries will be led by their commerce secretaries in
the talks.
</P>
<P>
As a land-locked country, Nepal largely depends on the transit
routes through India for foreign trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
