<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Petroleum-Chemical Seminar Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- An international seminar on
China's petroleum and chemical industries, the third since 1994,
opened today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The seminar attracted Chinese government officials and
representatives from petroleum, chemical, financial and consulting
sectors in more than 20 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has adopted a series of measures to
offset losses resulting from financial crisis in Asia and ensure
the stable and sustained growth of the nation's petrochemical
industry, according to Li Yongwu, director of the State Petroleum
and Chemical Industry Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Li said China has adopted measure to maintain the stability of
the Renminbi, increase investments in infrastructure and basic
industries, and strengthen the battle against smuggling.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is expected to help expand cooperation between
China's petroleum and chemical industries and overseas
counterparts, according to bureau official Liu Xiaobin.
</P>
<P>
The China Petroleum and Natural Gas Group and China Petroleum
and Chemical Industry Group were formed in July, and now boast
capital assets of well over 400 billion yuan. Liu said the groups
must introduce expertise, foreign investment and technology in
order to promote development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
