<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Increases Flood Relief Donations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Civil Affairs
today received yet another flood relief donation of 33 million
HK dollars (4.28 million U.S. dollars) from the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
HKSAR Secretary of Home Affairs David Lan presented the
Minister of Civil Affairs Doje Cering. Lan also conveyed the
concern and best wishes Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa and Hong
Kong citizens have expressed for flood victims.
</P>
<P>
Lan noted the funds were raised by a number of charitable
organizations and the Tung Wah Hospitals Group and Television
Broadcasts Limited of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong organization have donated well over 400 million HK
dollars to flood-devastated areas in central and northeastern
provinces.
</P>
<P>
Lan pointed to the inspiring philanthropic nature of Hong Kong
residents who have donated generously in spite of financial
difficulties facing the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
Cering praised Hong Kong compatriots for their generous
assistance to disaster relief efforts and pledged that all
donations will reach those in need.  
</P>
</TEXT>
