<HEADLINE> Decision to Abolish Madagascar-Taiwan Special Arrangement Welcomed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- China appreciates and
welcomes the decision made by Madagascar cabinet on September 9 to
abolish the Madagascar-Taiwan Special Arrangement signed in 1990,
said Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao
</P>
<P>
Asked to comment on the decision at a regular press conference
here this afternoon, Zhu said that the decision will certainly
benefit the smooth development of the friendly and cooperative
relations between China and Madagascar.
</P>
<P>
"The acts of splitting the motherland by the Taiwan authorities
are becoming more and more unpopular in the international
community," Zhu noted, adding that the practise of the "pragmatic
diplomacy" of the Taiwan authorities "has been boycotted and
opposed" by many countries around the world.
</P>
<P>
These facts fully demonstrated that the attempts and activities
of the Taiwan authorities, which run counter to the "one China"
policy, are doomed to fail, the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
