<DOCNO> XIE19980917.0211 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Local Authority Workers End Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Israeli local authority
workers called off their strike on Thursday, citing "substantial
progress" in talks with the Finance Ministry over their demands
for wage increase.
</P>
<P>
Trade Union of Israeli Local Authorities told Israel Radio
that it hold an over-night negotiation with the Finance Ministry
in an effort to end the strike.
</P>
<P>
During the talks the ministry still insisted that it would
accept a wage increase not more than 27.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
But it agreed to continue discussions with the trade union on
their demand for a 30 percent wage rise.
</P>
<P>
Leon Morozovsky, head of the trade union, said after the talks
that "we will be able to sign an agreement within a few days and I
therefore see no reason to continue the strike."
</P>
<P>
He also said that the strike was "worthwhile" and the trade
union "achieved substantial benefits for the workers".
</P>
<P>
The trade union launched the strike on Tuesday, which kept
some 100,000 employees of the local authorities throughout the
country from their work.
</P>
<P>
The strike shut down most of the municipal departments,
hospitals and kindergartens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
