<DOCNO> XIE19980917.0213 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Rehabilitation to Cost 900m Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The post-flood rehabilitation
in Bangladesh will cost more than 900 million U.S. dollars, The
Financial Express reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The cost estimate for the rehabilitation program was made on
the basis of primary findings, the report quoted a source as
saying.
</P>
<P>
A concrete rehabilitation plan will incorporate repair and
rehabilitation of surface infrastructure, supply of various kinds
of relief materials, support to farmers and other aspects, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Income-generating activities, health and education, repair of
roads and railways and support for agriculture will receive
priority, he stated.
</P>
<P>
The formulation of the rehabilitation program is already under
way, and a move has already been taken to mobilize funds
internally for the program, according to the source.
</P>
<P>
The government has already received commitments of over 170
million dollars' worth of materials from donor countries and
international organizations, he said.
</P>
<P>
Damage to the road infrastructure was extensive, with the cost
of restoring the road network estimated at around 20 billion taka
(about 425.5 million dollars), he stated.
</P>
<P>
The Planning Ministry has finalized paper work for diverting at
least 4 billion taka (about 85.11 million dollars) to the
post-flood rehabilitation program, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Ministry is also working on how to release funds
from the annual budget for the rehabilitation work, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
