<P>
PANAMA CITY -- Panama's banana export registered a 28 percent
decrease in the first eight months of 1998, according to
statistics published on Wednesday by the Industry and Trade
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Panama exported 15.875 million boxes of bananas (18.14
kilograms per box) during the period, 28 percent down from the 22
million mark in the same period of 1997. (Panama-Banana Exports)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
