<P>
COLOMBO -- Sri Lanka's gross domestic product (GDP) grew by
5.1 percent during the first half of this year, the Central Bank
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The GDP in real terms went up by 4.4 percent during the second
quarter of 1998 in contrast to the 5.8-percent growth in the first
 quarter. (Sri Lanka-GDP Growth)
</P>
