<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Introduces New Telecommunications Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has just launched two
telecommunications services linking the Chinese capital with
Australia.
</P>
<P>
The project, sponsored by the Beijing Municipal
Telecommunications Bureau and Telstra Corp. Ltd. of Australia,
will provide telecommunications services using frame relay and the
Integrated Service Digital Network (ISDN).
</P>
<P>
Frame relay is an exchange service featuring the rapid
classification of information into different grouping and the
capacity to handle emergency data.
</P>
<P>
ISDN, a versatile service which offers voice, data and visual
images via the same telephone line, can be connected to
telephones, fax machines, data terminals and multimedia
computers. The network also offers visual phones, long-distance
medical consulting and teaching services.
</P>
<P>
The network also links Beijing with the United States, Japan,
Germany, Singapore, the Republic of Korea, Switzerland, Britain,
Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The services has been introduced to a number of Chinese cities,
including Beijing, Guangzhou, Shanghai, Nanjing, Zhengzhou, Jinan
and Tianjin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
