<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poland Customs Seize 7 Kilograms of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Polish customs officers on
Sunday seized seven kilograms of cocaine in a town near Germany,
the Polish Press Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The illegal drug was found in a car owned by two Polish men
from northern city Gdansk, who were apparently heading into
Germany. They were arrested on drug trafficking charges.
</P>
<P>
Among recent drug seizures, a customs official was quoted as
saying, this is the biggest in the country's western border area.
</P>
<P>
As cocaine is the most expensive drug in Poland, where a gram
could sell for 200-400 zlotys (56-116 U.S. dollars) on the street,
the latest seizure may worth one million zlotys (280,000 dollars)
for drug wholesalers.
</P>
<P>
It might have come from South America, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Recent years have seen Poland being turned into a major transit
place for narcotics targeting West Europe and North America. In
1997, 16 kilograms of cocaine were seized in Poland, about 10
percent of the total seized in Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
