<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Parliament Regulates Advertisement Broadcasting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Bulgarian Parliament
Wednesday set a new strict regulation for advertising, limiting
its time and sponsorship, during the second reading of the bill on
radio and television.
</P>
<P>
The new regulation stipulates that during the prime time (19:00
to 22:00), the Bulgarian Nation Television, the official central
television station, is not allowed to air commercials for five
minutes non-stop or over four minutes per hour.
</P>
<P>
Other official stations, including the Bulgarian National
Radio, are not allowed to advertise over six minutes per hour.
</P>
<P>
As for the commercial stations, they are allowed to give over
12 minutes per hour or 15 percent of a day's air time to the
commercials.
</P>
<P>
The regulation also stipulates that no political parties,
organizations as well as religious groups should sponsor
advertisements or influence their content and presentation.
</P>
<P>
No national emblem, national anthem, images of state leaders
and broadcasting program hosts should be exploited, and cigarette
and drugs promoted, in the advertisements.
</P>
<P>
The regulation banned advertisements during national
celebrations and religious activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
