<HEADLINE> Kings Offer Adelman Head Coaching Job </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Sacramento Kings, who
have been looking for a coach since firing Eddie Jordan last
month, Wednesday offered the job to former Portland Trail Blazers
and Golden State Warriors coach Rick Adelman.
</P>
<P>
Kings director of media relations Troy Hanson confirmed that
the job has been offered to Adelman and that "the major points of
the contract have been agreed upon".
</P>
<P>
The 52-year-old Adelman was considered the only candidate for
the vacant coaching position at Portland State University, which
has been searching for a head coach since Ritchie McKay left for
Colorado States last month.
</P>
<P>
Adelman was out of coaching this past season after getting
fired by the Warriors following a 30-52 campaign in 1996-97. He
had two seasons remaining on a four-year, 4 million U.S. dollars
contract.
</P>
<P>
Adelman served as an assistant with the Trail Blazers for
five years before becoming head coach on February 19, 1989. He
guided the team to the NBA Finals in his first full season and ag
ain two years later in 1991-92.
</P>
<P>
Overall, in five-plus years in Portland, Adelman compiled a
291-154 record, including league-best 63-19 mark during the
1990-91 campaign.
</P>
<P>
The Kings have made the playoffs just once since the 1986-87
season and has won only one playoff game since losing in the
Western Conference finals against the Houston Rockets in 1981.
</P>
</TEXT>
