<HEADLINE> Don King's Lawsuit Can't Stop Chavez-Hoya Fight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Promoter Don King failed
to stop Julio Cesar Chavez to fight with Oscar De La Hoya when he
used his contract dispute to accuse the boxer, an appeals court
ruled Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
King and Chavez are entangled in a battle over an exclusive
contract the boxer signed with Don King Productions Inc. in 1997.
</P>
<P>
After he signed with King, Chavez agreed to a two-bout deal
with Top Rank Inc. and sued over his agreement with King.
</P>
<P>
King countered with his own suit, accusing Chavez of breach of
contract and asking a judge to keep Chavez out of the ring for
the Top Rank bouts.
</P>
<P>
King canceled a hearing to prevent Chavez's first fight in
June, but renewed the request in August for the De La Hoya fight.
Chavez and De La Hoya meet in rematch in Las Vegas on Friday
night.
</P>
<P>
A Broward County judge said there was no reason to prevent
Chavez from fighting because King could not show the company had
suffered irreparable harm. The 4th District Court of Appeal
Wednesday agreed with the trial judge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
