<HEADLINE> Banana Export in Panama Down 28 Percent in Eight Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Panama's banana export
registered a 28 percent decrease in the first eight months of
1998, according to statistics published on Wednesday by the
Industry and Trade Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Panama exported 15.875 million boxes of bananas (18.14
kilograms per box) during the period, 28 percent down from the 22
million mark in the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Banana export earns the country more than 120 million dollars
every year, the second largest earner after shrimp export, which
also lost 30 million dollars in the period.
</P>
<P>
The ministry attributed the decrease to the 57-day strike of
1,500 workers for salaries increase. 
</P>
</TEXT>
