<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Artists Set Record in Famous-Painting Replica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Three young Chinese artists
spent 16 months to complete a replica of the world famous
painting "Mona Lisa" using over 240,000 pieces of colorful stones.
</P>
<P>
This replica was recently confirmed as the largest of its kind
in the world by the Shanghai Office of the Guiness Book of World
Records.
</P>
<P>
The three artists live in the city of Shantou in south China's
Guangdong Province and invested 220,000 yuan in this
project. Their construction is 12.3 meters long and 8.2 meters
wide, with a total surface area 271.86 times that of the original
painting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
