<HEADLINE> Sichuan Strengthens Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
Province has launched 12 environmental protection projects with a
total investment of 340 million yuan (about 45 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The projects include garbage treatment plants in Jiuzhaigou and
Neijiang and waste water treatment plants in Mianyang and
Chengdu.
</P>
<P>
After the completion of these projects, the ecological
surroundings of the Mingjiang and Tuojiang river valleys, and the
city of Jiuzhaigou, one of the most famous scenic spots in China,
will be much improved.  
</P>
