<HEADLINE> Olympic Champion Wang Junxia Leaves for America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Women's 5,000 meters Olympic
champion Wang Junxia, companied by her newly-married husband Zhan
Yu, left here on Wednesday for the United States to study in the
Colorado State University.
</P>
<P>
"I accepted the invitation from the University earlier when
I  thought everything is OK there", said Wang, the former most
famous member of Ma's Family Army, though she must pay the
tuition by herself.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who has not appeared in the track since the end of the
Atlanta Olympic Games, said she will resume training in the
University if her health permits.
</P>
<P>
"If I could really resume training and my result is
satisfaction, I hope I can have a chance to win honor again for
the country," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Wang, nicknamed "Oriental Mysterious Deer", rose to fame in
the 1993 World Athletic Championships in Stuttgart, Germany, by
winning the women's 10,000 meters event, in which she still holds
the world record.
</P>
<P>
The Liaoning native split from coach Ma Junren in 1994 along
with her world champion teammate Liu Dong in a dispute over the
prize money from the Stuttgart world championships.  
</P>
</TEXT>
