<HEADLINE> Western Countries Top Investment In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The volume of
U.S. investments in Beijing jumped three-fold during the first
eight months of the year, with European investments in the Chinese
capital rising 1.6-fold.
</P>
<P>
Asian countries accounted for the slowest growth rate in
investments, with the rate for the period growing by only 20
percent.
</P>
<P>
Beijing recorded 1.54 billion U.S. dollars in foreign
investment, representing a 62.27 percent rise in the increase rate
for total foreign investments for the period, according to
statistics from the Beijing Foreign Economic Relations and Trade
Commission.
</P>
<P>
Beijing approved 457 foreign-funded enterprises, up 9.1 percent
on the 1997 period.  
</P>
