<HEADLINE> Italy Returns Historic Relics to Latin American Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Italy's financial police
returned hundreds of historic relics to six Latin American
countries in Milan Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At a hand-over ceremony attended by representatives from Peru,
Mexico, Colombia, Costa Rica, Ecuador and Guatemala, the police
gave back to these countries 521 pieces of historic relics,
including potteries and vases dating back to several hundred years
before Christ.
</P>
<P>
An anonymous businessman of Milan bought about 1,500 items of
relics in the Latin American countries, with 1,295 of them finding
their way illegally into Italy and confiscated by police.
</P>
<P>
Experts confirmed that these 521 items belong to the six
countries, and after further identification, the remaining 774
items will also be returned to their home countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
