<HEADLINE> Clinton Pledges to Help Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
told his Brazilian counterpart Fernando Henrique Cardoso that the
U.S. would not hesitate to help Brazil and other Latin American
countries avoid a financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Clinton made the statement Wednesday on the phone with the
Brazilian president after most Latin American stock markets
plummeted last week, a spokesman for president Sergio Amaral said.
</P>
<P>
President Clinton also praised Cardoso's management of his
country's economy and highlighted the importance of a stable
currency, reforms and modernization of the Brazilian economy.
</P>
<P>
Cardoso briefed Clinton on Brazil's economic situation and
assured him that his determination to defend the currency is real.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that President Cardoso was very happy to see
the positive turn in the financial markets because of measures
taken by the government to keep the financial markets stable and
avoid the bad effects of the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
For the past three days, the Brazilian stock markets have gone
up after hitting a record low last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
