<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Pentathletes Stamp Their Authority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- China stamped their
authority with a swaggering performance, leaving only one gold
for their rivals to vie at the CISM 46th Military Pentathlon
World Championships ended on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The host celebrated its dominance with four new world records
and five of the six gold medals, including a 1-2-3 finish in the
women's individual and top four places in the men's part.
</P>
<P>
The replies of other countries were a women's cross-country
new world record by Ilona Lubane of Latvia and a men's obstacles
relay race title taken by Turkey.
</P>
<P>
"China will stay atop in the competition for next five to ten
years," said Hartmut Nienaber, German former men's ten-time world
champion.
</P>
<P>
China's team leader Jiao Liming said, "Most of the old
competitors, like Yang Chunyi,, Guo Xinqiao, Wang Lianying who
won the women's individual gold medal for five consecutive times
with the new world record, will retire after next year's
competition in Croatia. But we're confident to maintain our best
for the sport."
</P>
<P>
Brazil, winner of last year's men's individual in Sweden,
brought home the silver medal and fourth.
</P>
<P>
While in the women's competition, Denmark was embarrassed
everytime by China to finish two second places in the team
competition and the relay race, and fifth place following the
Chinese leading four in individual. 
</P>
</TEXT>
