<HEADLINE> Temple Displays Inscribed Theater Boards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Zhihua Temple is
currently displaying 71 inscribed theater boards dating from the
Qing Dynasty (1644-1911) to the first half of this century.
</P>
<P>
The boards are inscribed with odes for the gods and list of
people in theatrical troupes.
</P>
<P>
The boards contain the names of more than 3,000 Peking Opera
performers.
</P>
<P>
Historians say the boards provide valuable material for
research into the history of Peking Opera. 
</P>
