<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Nanning, capital of south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, will host its second
international educational products trade fair for students between
October 9-12.
</P>
<P>
Over 500 enterprises from both at home and abroad have
registered to attend the fair.
</P>
<P>
Last year's fair recorded a total transaction volume of 500
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The fairs represent part of the city's efforts to transform
itself into a production center for related products. Nanning has
also invested over 300 million yuan to build a products exhibition
center covering 40 hectares. 
