items in leading Australian newspapers Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian:
</P>
<P>
-- Australian Treasurer Peter Costello Wednesday challenged
wide-spread fears that Australia is heading for a crippling
economic slump, suggesting the economy could pick up speed as
early as next year after a temporary slowdown.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney Morning Herald:
</P>
<P>
-- Australian Prime Minister John Howard has conceded that tax
reform may cost his government the election to be held on October
3 as he was forced to defend his tax package against a scathing
assessment Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
