</P>
<P>
-- Australian Deputy Prime Minister Tim Fischer, whose party
represents farmers, Wednesday tried to avoid a face-to-face
meeting with a leading member of One Nation Party after being
jeered and heckled by 200 angry farmers in Yass, a small town in
the New South Wales state.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review:
</P>
<P>
-- Australian-New Zealand airline Ansett has launched a
three-year drive to revive the company's earnings with plans to
radically overhaul its regional operations, acquire 180 million
U.S. dollars' worth of new jets and exit its fourth Asian market.
