<DOCNO> XIE19980917.0300 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Olano Stays ahead in Tour of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Abraham Olano held off tough
challenge to stay ahead at the Tour of Spain on Wednesday after a
spectacular 11th stage from the Andorran frontier to Cerler,
Spain.
</P>
<P>
While the Spaniard's lieutenant Jose Maria Jimenez foiled the
plans of Fernando Escartin for a second day to score his third
stage win in six days, 1995 Tour of Spain winner Laurent Jalabert
struck in the closing kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Attacking in the last kilometer, the Frenchman finished sixth,
13 seconds behind Jimenez, and trimmed six seconds from Olano's
overnight advantage of 41 seconds.
</P>
<P>
He is now 35 seconds behind Olano overall.
</P>
<P>
Escartin was third behind teammate Roberto Heras after the
186km race, and closed to within 51 seconds of the race leader in
third place overall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980917.0301 </DOCNO>
