<HEADLINE> Iran to Launch Maneuvers in Persian Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Iran announced on Wednesday
to launch a week-long naval maneuvers in the Persian Gulf
next week.
</P>
<P>
Deputy commander of the first zone of the Iranian army's
naval force Habibollah Sayyari said that the maneuvers with a
code name Me'raj (ascension) would be held around Qeshm island
in the Persian Gulf.
</P>
<P>
According to the official news agency IRNA, Sayyari did not
mention the exact date of the maneuver but said that the goal
behind the maneuvers was to raise the naval forces' combat
readiness.
</P>
<P>
Naval and aviation fleets as well as the special operations'
parachutists and frogmen of the Iranian army are to take part at
the war games, he said.
</P>
<P>
The official also said that certain forces involved in the
maneuvers would participate in Zolfeqar-2 maneuvers to be held by
the army's ground forces on the eastern border with Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
He did not specify number of the participant fleets and number
of the forces involved in the war games.
</P>
<P>
Iranian army announced earlier to hold its biggest maneuvers
on the eastern border with the participation of 200,000 troops
following the tension between Iran and the Afghan Taliban militia.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban killed eight Iranian diplomats and a correspondent
of the official news agency IRNA in Mazari Sharif on August 8 when
the group occupied the city in northern Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Iran has warned to take revenge on the Taliban for killing
Iranian diplomats and reporter. 
</P>
