<HEADLINE> Sudan Claims Killing 50 Ugandans, Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Sudanese forces have
managed to repulsed a Ugandan-led offensive in southern Sudan,
killing 50 people, mostly Ugandan soldiers, according to a
statement issued Wednesday by the Sudanese armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese General Command of the People`s Armed Forces said
in the statement that the Ugandan troops started on Monday
sporadic artillery attacks against the Sudanese forces camps in
southern Sudanese areas which border Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The Ugandan troops started an intensive and repetitive attack
with tanks, armors and infantry on some points in these areas,
the statement said, adding that the Sudanese forces managed to
stop the offensives courageously through fierce fighting.
</P>
<P>
It said that the intensive battles claimed the fives of 50
people, mostly Ugandan troops and Sudanese rebels.
</P>
<P>
Three Sudanese soldiers were also killed and five other
injured in the clashes, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese forces succeeded in destroying three tanks, three
armors and an ammunition vehicle.
</P>
<P>
The statement noted that the fighting was still going on in
certain areas to fight back the Ugandan troops and Sudanese rebels.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese-Ugandan relations have strained after both
countries accusing each other of supporting each other's
insurgents. 
