<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2025GMT, September 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- As their strike entered the second day Wednesday,
Israeli local authority workers threatened to intensify it if
demands for wage increase were not met.
</P>
<P>
Trade Union of Israeli Local Authorities said that it had hold
negotiations with the Finance Ministry Tuesday night in an effort
to reach an agreement and end the strike.
</P>
<P>
However, it said, the officials from the ministry still refused
to give a 30 percent wage rise as the trade union suggested after
five hours of talks. (Israel-Strike)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The Arab League (AL) will present a new initiative on
Somalia at the 110th session of the AL Foreign Ministerial Council
conference, which is to be held in Cairo Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
AL Assistant Secretary General Ahmed bin Hilli said that the
impetus for the new initiative was based on an agreement signed
last month by rival factions of the Somali National Alliance and the
26-faction National Salvation Council. (AL-Somalia-Fresh-Initiative)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Palestinian National Authority President Yasser Arafat
Wednesday morning held talks with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
on his recent contacts made to break the peace impasse with
Israel, the Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Arafat arrived in the northern coastal city of Alexandria
Tuesday evening on a two-day visit to Egypt to attend the Arab
League (AL) Foreign Ministers' meeting. (Egypt-Mubarak-Arafat)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Foreign ministers from the 22 Arab League (AL) member
states met Wednesday at its headquarters in Cairo to coordinate
stances on vital issues challenging the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
At the 110th session of the AL Foreign Ministerial Council
meeting, the ministers will discuss draft resolutions, which
reaffirm the land-for-peace principle and the Palestinians' rights
to self-determination, and call on the world community to impose
"appropriate sanctions" against Israel. (AL-Council Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- As U.S. Middle East peace envoy Dennis Ross is
winding up his mission in the region with no imminent breakthrough
in sight, Israel and the Palestinians are drawing different
conclusions over his mediating efforts.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio reported Wednesday that Palestinian National
Authority President Yasser Arafat has described Ross' visit as a
failure, saying it had not yielded any result.
</P>
<P>
The radio quoted Arafat as telling an Egyptian newspaper that
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu had attempted to
destroy the peace process by procrastinating and dodging issues
concerning the overdue Israeli withdrawal from the West Bank.
(Israel-Palestinians-Ross)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi on Wednesday
stressed that priority should be given to political and peaceful
means rather than military actions against the Afghan Taliban
militia.
</P>
<P>
"Before taking military actions against the Taliban, a chance
should be given to political and peaceful approaches in order to
protect the country's national interests," Kharrazi told the
official news agency IRNA.
(Iran-FM-Taliban)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Palestinian National Authority President Yasser Arafat
Wednesday stressed his determination to declare an independent
Palestinian state in 1999 and called for a new Arab summit to
tackle the Mideast peace crisis.
</P>
<P>
In his address to the opening of the 110th Arab League Foreign
Ministerial Council meetings, Arafat appealed to Arab and Islamic
countries to buttress up the Palestinian aspiration for setting up
their own state with Jerusalem as its capital.
(Egypt-Arafat-Arab Ministers)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- The only Iranian diplomat who survived the massacre
by the Afghan Taliban militia appeared on Iran's state-run
television Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Allahdad Shahsavan Qare-Husseini, head of the secretariat of
the Iranian consulate in Mazari Sharif and in charge of the
refugee affairs, was shot and wounded in the massacre on August
8, but survived the killing.
(Iran-Diplomat-On TV)
</P>
<P>
